The four matches concerned are Manchester United’s trip to Southampton on December 8, Queens Park Rangers facing Everton at Goodison a week later, Chelsea visiting Stoke on December 22, and Swansea taking on Liverpool at Anfield two days before New Year’s Eve.

Alan Lewis, chair of Swansea City Supporters’ Trust, said there was ‘sufficient evidence to suggest travelling fans are not really considered when the fixtures are changed’.

There was also a backlash on Twitter, with Chelsea fan William McIntyre writing:

‘Stoke away moved to a Monday night, 3 days before Christmas. Thank you very much Sky, always putting the fans first....’

Phil Blanco, a Manchester United supporter, posted: ‘Southampton away 8pm on a Monday night. Consideration given to travelling fans there eh Sky?’

