BT Sport have two evening games in December but they are during the midweek when night fixtures were scheduled to take place in any case.

Liverpool’s trip to Leicester on December 2 is impossible to get back from the same night using public transport but Southampton’s visit to Arsenal has frequent trains running up until midnight without changes, available at reasonable cost.

A spokesman for BT Sport said: ‘Fixture scheduling is a complex process involving multiple parties - clubs, broadcasters, police and local authorities - and all sign off match selections. We always strive to balance local and fan needs alongside the need to schedule games for the benefit of our viewers.’

 

